ct (a valid 'no fix needed, here's the guard + reasoning' outcome).\n\n## ADR-0003 (Accepted) — Context / Decision / Consequences\nWritten to `docs/adr/ADR-0003-test-the-getmatches-assembly-boundary.md`, building on ADR-0001. Judged against the existing pure-function feature-module architecture: no new deps, no API change. It also documents an intentional inconsistency the tests now pin — `getMatches` does not reformat ISO close dates while `deadline-radar` parses both.\n\n## Verification\n```chart\nNew tests added: 8\nDefects found: 0\nFull suite tests passing: 202\n```\nFull suite green: **19 files / 202 tests** (was 18/194). `tsc --noEmit` clean.\n\n## Task breakdown — 4 tasks, 8 points (4 delivered this run)\n| # | Task | Pts | Status |\n|---|------|-----|--------|\n| 1 | Empty-DB, `total>0` filter, fit-desc ordering, limit | 2 | ✅ done |\n| 2 | `GrantMatch` mapping/formatting + truncation | 2 | ✅ done |\n| 3 | Cover grants.gov network fetch paths (mock `fetch`) — carried from ADR-0001 task 4 | 2 | scoped |\n| 4 | Unify close-date formatting between `getMatches` and `deadline-radar` (or document divergence) | 2 | scoped |\n\nTasks 3–4 (4 pts) are scoped for a delivery agent and emitted on `architecture.analysis.completed`.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "high"}}

