ill delete *any* attachment by id regardless of owner. On a multi-tenant or public deploy this is full unauthenticated read/write/delete of grant data + uploads.\n- **Severity rationale:** Auth findings err high. Caveat: this is clearly **intentional v0** (code comments: *\"v1 keys this off the session user\"*, singleton-org demo on local SQLite). Reported as High because it is **blocking before any non-local / multi-user deploy**, not because the current local demo is under attack.\n- **Fix:** Add a session/auth gate to all server actions before v1; scope `deleteAttachment` (and reads) by the active `orgId` so a row can only be touched by its owner.\n\n---\n\n## Medium\n\n### M1 — `postcss` flagged by npm audit (transitive via `next`)\n**`package.json`** — `postcss ^8.5.15` (+ `autoprefixer`). `npm audit --omit=dev` reports **2 moderate**: *\"PostCSS XSS via Unescaped `` in CSS Stringify Output.\"*\n- **Risk:** Build-time CSS tooling; real-world runtime exposure is limited (no untrusted CSS is stringified at runtime in this app). Reported regardless of reachability per dependency-CVE policy.\n- **Fix:** `npm audit fix`; pin `postcss` to the patched release the advisory names. Re-run `npm audit` to confirm 0.\n\n---\n\n## Low\n\n### L1 — Dynamic DDL string interpolation in migration helper\n**`src/features/drafts/storage.ts:39,42`** — `db.prepare(\\`PRAGMA table_info(${table})\\`)` and `db.exec(\\`ALTER TABLE ${table} ADD COLUMN ${column} ${decl}\\`)`.\n- **Risk:** Latent SQL injection **only if** `table`/`column`/`decl` ever take untrusted input. Today the single caller passes **hardcoded literals** (`\"drafts\"`, `\"awarded_amount_usd\"`, `\"INTEGER\"`) → **not currently exploitable**.\n- **Fix:** Keep these arguments restricted to a hardcoded allowlist; add a comment/assert so a future caller can't pass user data into the DDL.\n\n---\n\n## Verified clean (no findings)\n- **SQL:** all runtime queries across `*/storage.ts` use parameterized `.prepare(... ?).run(...